'author_association': 'NONE', 'active_lock_reason': None, 'body': "Hey folks, I've started using this site for tracking my Pokemon in Home and BDSP and wanted to share my thoughts on how tracking should work for PLA.

I would like to be able to break out the tasks for each Pokemon individually so I can put in the exact number that I currently have and have the website be able to calculate the current research level. There are probably several degrees of completion that should be tracked: research level 10 and perfect. I think these are two separate goals that people may want to achieve, and even then may want to focus on one or the other.

It may also be useful to track simply which ones have been caught in general so I as the player know where to start: my pasture or the world.

I haven't seen any other discussions on PLA yet, so I just wanted to open this to give some suggestions and discuss other ideas.
